Build ubuntu-oracular sdcard for raspberrypi5:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-oracular/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-ubuntu-oracular/linaro-rootfs.img

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://github.com/pftf/RPi4/releases/download/v1.38/RPi4_UEFI_Firmware_v1.38.zip

cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/ubuntu-oracular

Plugin sdcard to PC.
sudo ./mkuefiboot.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
sudo mount -t vfat /dev/sda1 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi4_UEFI_Firmware_v1.38.zip
cd ~/build-raspberrypi5/ubuntu-oracular
sync
sudo umount /mnt
Eject sdcard from PC.

Plugin USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mkusbssd.sh
Eject USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin sdcard and USB2-SATA-SSD to rpi5.
Esc -> Device Manager -> Rpi -> Advanced -> 3GB ( disable ) -> F10 -> Boot Manager -> first UEFI.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sudo vi /etc/systemd/logind.conf ( change to follows:
HandlePowerKey=ignore
HandleRebootKey=ignore
HandleSuspendKey=ignore
HandleHibernateKey=ignore
HandleLidSwitch=ignore
)
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install firefox-esr
firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4
mpv swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
